FAQs

Quick Ride is a leading outstation taxi service provider in the country. We are available in 7 major cities and experiencing rapid growth. We offer the most competitive outstation cab charges without any hidden fees or surprises. Our fleet consists of the latest car models, providing a wide variety of options to suit your budget and travel needs. We ensure the quality and hygiene of our cars through regular inspections. Our experienced, professional, and courteous drivers are our unique selling point. We provide personalized customer support throughout your journey with us. When you book with us, you can trust that your outstation trip is in capable hands.

We provide four categories of cars for outstation bookings. You can choose from the following options:
Hatchback - Tata Indica, WagonR or similar.
Sedan - Tata Tigor, Swift Dzire, Toyota Etios or similar.
SUV - Xylo, Ertiga, Marazzo or similar.
SUV Luxury - Innova , Innova Crysta or similar

Note: Toll and state charges may be included for certain routes, and they will be reflected in your booking quotation as well as in your invoice.

You need to pay just 20% of the total trip fare at the time of booking. You can pay the rest after the completion of the ride.

Quick Ride supports all major online digital payment platforms like PayTm, Amazon Pay, Phone Pe etc. You can also pay using your Credit/Debit cards.
Important: All the cash transactions made directly to the driver during your outstation trip must be recorded in the Quick Ride app.

An additional allowance will be applicable and must be paid to the driver for driving between 10:00 PM and 06:00 AM on any of the nights.
(Check table above for night time driver allowance charges as per car type)

All the cars we provide undergo a pre-examination for quality and condition. However, if an unexpected breakdown occurs during your journey, we will make every effort to arrange another vehicle of the same category for you. Alternatively, you have the option to be refunded based on the distance covered.

Any additional or incidental charges must be Recorded by the driver in the app and require the customer's approval. If there are any cash transactions, you can register them in the Quick Ride app, and they will be adjusted accordingly in the final invoice.

The initial bill covers the fixed distance and driver allowance, while the final bill includes charges like tolls, state taxes, night driving allowance, and extra kilometer fare. The invoice provides a detailed breakdown of these charges. For any inquiries, please reach out to our team at support@quickride.in or call at 080 468 10628.

Outstation bookings can be cancelled up to 4 hours prior to the pickup time without charges. Cancellation fees apply for cancellations within this time frame, ranging from â¹100 to 20% of the total trip fare. Quick Ride compensates customers if a driver cancels a trip after accepting it.

We are just a tap away 24/7 in case you have any concerns regarding your safety, confusions, emergency and driver behaviour related issues.
